17 TV series)\n|EpisodeNumber   = 47\n|EpisodeNumber2  = 8\n|Title           = Enid's Last Race\n|DirectedBy      = Dermot Boyd\n|WrittenBy       = Paul Gerstenberger\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|16|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/schedules/p00fzl9r/2020/03/16|title=BBC TV Guide|website=bbc.co.uk|access-date=9 March 2020}}</ref>\n|Viewers         =\n|ShortSummary    = A disheartened Enid leaves Cackles Academy after being tricked into stealing Miss Drill's speed potion formula. She rehearses with her eager mother for \"The Deadly Nightshades and family\" show. Miss Drill does not blame Enid and (along with Mildred) persuades her to take part in the Witch World Games qualifiers. Meanwhile Miss Tapioca, Mr Daisy, and students rustle up ingredients for Miss Drill's potion which helps Enid to win, despite sneaky tricks by Miss Hempnettle. Enid accepts a place at the prestigious Mount Broom sporting academy now with the encouragement of her mother. In a sub-plot Ethel undermines Azura as a school ambassador to the Magic Council.\n|LineColor       = #904000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Worst Witch (2017 TV series)\n|EpisodeNumber   = 48\n|EpisodeNumber2  = 9\n|Title           = Mildred the Detective\n|DirectedBy      = Dermot Boyd\n|WrittenBy       = Kirstie Falkous & Neil Jones\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|23|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/schedules/p00fzl9r/2020/03/23|title=BBC TV Guide|website=bbc.co.uk|access-date=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n|Viewers         =\n|ShortSummary    = Ethel accuses Mildred of taking her head girl badges. A locating crystal leads Ethel to find them on the roof. Many other strange events occur around the academy like the broom store, kitchen and library all in a mess. Miss Cackle assigns Mildred and Ethel the head-girl-competition task of discovering the prankster. Meanwhile Fenella is too controlling in her dining etiquette project (plus sabotage by the prankster) results in the coven leaving her. Mildred sees an unattached shadow of Azura's silhouette, leading to the revelation Azura had cast a spell to rid herself of scary dark shadows: her own became detached causing the events. Mildred volunteers to take the blame, and Miss Hardbroom says this is evidence of head girl material. Meanwhile Mr Daisy is up to something secretive in a shed, but what?\n|LineColor       = #904000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Worst Witch (2017 TV series)\n|EpisodeNumber   = 49\n|EpisodeNumber2  = 10\n|Title           = A Witch in Time\n|DirectedBy      = Lindy Heymann\n|WrittenBy       = Scott Payne\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|30|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/schedules/p00fzl9r/2020/03/30|title=BBC TV Guide|website=bbc.co.uk|access-date=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n|Viewers         =\n|ShortSummary    = Mildred and Ethel compete in the Head Girl competition Triathlon, Mildred wins chanting and flying but looses on control of her familiar Tabby. Worried her vision of Ethel making all the students disappear if she becomes head girl, Mildred uses a sandtimer to go back in time four times. Her three initial attempts all end in disaster (her dog raids the kitchen, Maud looses her voice, and next time injured). Fourthly, at Mr. Daisy's behest \"A great witch relies on her wits, not just her magic,\" Mildred wins the Triathlon. Meanwhile Mr Daisy's secret Patented Potions Machine is revealed and is sabotaged by Mabel, who eventually relents when Miss Hardbroom intends to sack him for incompetence.\n|LineColor       = #904000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Worst Witch (2017 TV series)\n|EpisodeNumber   = 50\n|EpisodeNumber2  = 11\n|Title           = Grounded\n|DirectedBy      = Lindy Heymann\n|WrittenBy       = Paul Gerstenberger\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|6|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/schedules/p00fzl9r/2020/04/06|title=BBC TV Guide|website=bbc.co.uk|access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n|Viewers         =\n|ShortSummary    = The arrival of a magical comet is announced. With Mildred and Ethel getting ready for the final head girl challenge (to create a new spell) Mildred starts to suffer from magical burnout. Knowing this Maud, Izzy and Mrs Cackle decide to send her to rest at Izzy's farm to watch the comet. Upon arriving Mildred's attempts at magic go wrong to the point of her magic completely failing. After a bit of digging it is found that Mildred needs her family's grounding stone to restore her magic, and since she has no idea where it is, Izzy's dad hatch's a plan to use the comet to create a new one.\nBack at the school Ethel tries to disqualify Mildred from the head girl competition by snitching on a half-heard conversation between Mildred and Professor Daisy when returning his sandtimer. Maud and Azura try to delay Ethel, this only works for a short while before Ethel brings Miss Hardbroom into it. This leads to a confrontation with Mr Daisy who ultimately protects Mildred by claiming he was the one to loop time. And come the end of term will be fired.\nBack at the farm Mildred and Izzy's attempts to create a new grounding stone ultimately fail, when all is assumed lost Mildred's true grounding stone is found as Izzy's dad (Spike Jones played by Alun Raglan) was given it by Mrs Hubble many years ago in Morroco. Mildred restores her magic and goes back to the academy with a good idea for her Spell.\n|LineColor       = #904000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Worst Witch (2017 TV series)\n|EpisodeNumber   = 51\n|EpisodeNumber2  = 12\n|Title           = The Witching Hour: Part 1\n|DirectedBy      = Lindy Heymann\n|WrittenBy       = Neil Jones\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|13|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/schedules/p00fzl9r/2020/04/13|title=BBC TV Guide|website=bbc.co.uk|access-date=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|Viewers         =\n|ShortSummary    = Ethel and Mildred perform their newly designed spells in the final round of the Head Girl competition. Mildred's spell apparently goes wrong and turns Headmistress Miss Cackle into shattered glass. Mildred is sent to The Correctional School for Undesirable Witches, Wormwood, where she is befriended by Camilla Clove (played by Madeleine Edmondson) and menaced by the cruel jailer Miss Splinter (played by Sue Vincent). Meanwhile Maud analyses playback and realises someone else caused Miss Cackle's demise and deliberately gets herself sent to Wormwood too with a plan to free Mildred. Ethel was doing Agatha (Ada's evil twin) Cackle's bidding and tricked Felicity into sabotaging Mildred's spell. Ethel frees Agatha. Mildred and Maud make their escape from Wormwood.\nIn a sub-plot, an attempt to comfort (the soon to be dismissed) Mr Daisy with a Happiness Potion goes wrong, when he dances in an over familiar way with Miss Hardbroom.\n|LineColor       = #904000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Worst Witch (2017 TV series)\n|EpisodeNumber   = 52\n|EpisodeNumber2  = 13\n|Title           = The Witching Hour: Part 2\n|DirectedBy      = Lindy Heymann\n|WrittenBy       = Neil Jones\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|20|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/schedules/p00fzl9r/2020/04/20|title=BBC TV Guide|website=bbc.co.uk|access-date=13 April 2020}}</ref>\n|Viewers         =\n|ShortSummary    = Agatha Cackle, impersonating headmistress Ada, promotes Ethel to head girl, and at the school assembly tricks everyone else into the Banishment plane of existence, including Mildred's mum (who had been messaged by Maud). Agatha locks Mr. Daisy away and thwarts Miss Hardbroom with a magic restricting broach. She also demands the Great Wizard hands over his title.\nMildred's mum organises tower building with junk in the banishment plane, and they escape. \n\nMildred and Maud search for the magic reversal word to reverse the banishment and in the process discover Mr. Daisy locked away. He agrees to use his potion machine, so while Mildred and Maud delay Agatha with distractions, his machine's potion restores Miss Cackle. She in turn saves Mildred's Mum with the secret word. Agatha banishes herself.\n\nMildred learns Izzy Jones is her sister and Spike is her dad, who her mum (Julie) met in Morrocco just before she was born. Mildred and Ethel make peace just before Mildred is confirmed as head girl.\n|LineColor       = #904000\n}}\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==Production and casting==\nIn November 2014, it was announced that a new series of The Worst Witch was in development with the [[British Broadcasting Corporation|BBC]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/news/a607329/the-worst-witch-writer-reveals-new-tv-adaptation-is-in-development/|title=The Worst Witch writer reveals new TV adaptation is in development|work=Digital Spy|last=Alexander|first=Susannah|date=2 November 2014|accessdate=6 January 2018}}</ref> The cast of the show was announced in October 2016.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/news/a812479/heres-your-first-look-at-the-spooky-worst-witch-tv-remake/|title=Here's your first look at the spooky Worst Witch TV remake, featuring stars from Game of Thrones and Downton Abbey|work=Digital Spy|last=Anderton|first=Joe|date=31 October 2016|accessdate=6 January 2018}}</ref> ''[[Game of Thrones]]'' actress [[Bella Ramsey]] was cast as Mildred and said filming the series \"was really good\", but there were some challenging elements and described learning the stunts as \"hard.\"<ref name=\"Bella Ramsey casting\">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2016/dec/18/worst-witch-children-tv-adaptation|title=Harry Potter for girls? I\u2019m not that kind of Worst Witch, says TV\u2019s new Mildred Hubble|work=Guardian|last=Conlan|first=Tara|date=25 July 2017|accessdate=6 January 2018}}</ref> Ramsey drew similarities between herself and Mildred.<ref name=\"Bella Ramsey casting\"/> Meibh Campbell played the role of Maud Spellbody for series 1, but was replaced by Megan Hughes from series 2.<ref name=\"Megan Hughes casting\">{{cite news|url=http://www.oxfordmail.co.uk/news/15428751.Oxfordshire_schoolgirl_set_to_become_national_star_in_new_series_of_The_Worst_Witch/|title=Oxfordshire schoolgirl Megan Hughes is set to become a national star in new series of The Worst Witch|work=Oxford Mail|last=Hughes|first=Pete|date=25 July 2017|accessdate=6 January 2018}}</ref> Of her casting, Hughes said working on the show is \"great and I [Hughes] love the experience\" and that she is \"so grateful for the opportunity.\" Hughes had two auditions before being offered the part of Maud.<ref name=\"Megan Hughes casting\"/> Hughes' mother, Claire, added that Hughes has an \"amazing time\" and is \"really happy, really positive\" throughout filming.<ref name=\"Megan Hughes casting\"/> Tamara Smart gained the part of Enid Nightshade after four months of auditioning, which she described as \"very long\" yet \"nerve racking but at the same time very exciting.\" Smart was excited about the \"amazing experience\" when she got the part.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.borehamwoodtimes.co.uk/news/14725970.Barnet_schoolgirl_is_flying_high_at_landing_star_role_in_CBBC_show/|title=Barnet schoolgirl is flying high at landing star role in CBBC show|work=Borehamwood Times|date=6 September 2016|accessdate=6 January 2018}}</ref> Jenny Richardson and Miriam Petche were cast as sisters Ethel and Esmerelda Hallow.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.yourlocalguardian.co.uk/news/14947530.Drama_pupil_from_Leatherhead_to_star_in_The_Worst_Witch_reboot/|title=Drama pupil from Leatherhead to star in The Worst Witch reboot|work=Your Local Guardian|last=Dickerson|first=Rachel|date=5 December 2016|accessdate=6 January 2018}}</ref><ref>[https://twitter.com/mark_jermin_mgt/status/733620874746732545 Mark Jermin Management on Twitter: HUGE well done to Miriam Petche who will be playing the role of Esmerelda in new CBBC remake of THE WORST WITCH!<!--Bot Generated Title-->]</ref> Tallulah Milligan, the daughter of ''[[Coronation Street]]'' and ''[[Waterloo Road (TV series)|Waterloo Road]]'' actress [[Angela Griffin]], was cast as Drusilla Paddock. Griffin said Milligan \"absolutely loves\" working on the show.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2016/jul/15/angela-griffin-shes-ace-my-mum-a-grounded-down-to-earth-yorkshirewoman|title=Angela Griffin: \u2018She\u2019s ace, my mum \u2013 a grounded, down-to-earth Yorkshirewoman\u2019|work=Guardian|last=Gray|first=Susan|date=16 July 2016|accessdate=6 January 2018}}</ref> Dagny Rollins plays the role of Felicity Foxglove.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/news/showbiz-news/leanne-brown-angela-griffin-cbbc-12310052|title=Leanne Brown and Angela Griffin turn out for special CBBC Worst Witch screening|work=Manchester Evening News|date=14 December 2016|accessdate=6 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe Worst Witch is filmed at [[Peckforton Castle]], [[Peckforton]] [[Cheshire]], [[England]] and [[Burg Hohenzollern]], [[Swabian Alps]], [[Germany]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/mediapacks/worstwitch/15-facts|title=CBBC brings The Worst Witch to life for a new generation|work=BBC|date=11 December 2016|accessdate=6 January 2018}}</ref> The second series is also filmed at [[Adlington Hall]], [[Adlington, Cheshire|Adlington]], [[Cheshire]], using their grand hall, minstrel's gallery and their countryside and woods backdrop.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://marketingcheshire.co.uk/news/adlington-hall-gardens-turns-witching-academy/|title=Adlington Hall & Gardens Turns Into A Witching Academy|work=Marketing Cheshire|year=2018|accessdate=12 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{BBC programme | b09m8lyz | The Worst Witch}}\n* [https://www.netflix.com/title/80130521''The Worst Witch''] on [[Netflix]]\n* {{IMDb title|5721172|The Worst Witch}}\n\n{{The Worst Witch}}\n{{Netflix original current series}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Worst Witch, The}}\n[[Category:BBC children's television programmes]]\n[[Category:ZDF television series]]\n[[Category:Witchcraft in television]]\n[[Category:Wizards in television]]\n[[Category:British supernatural television programmes]]\n[[Category:2017 British television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2010s British children's television series]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:The Worst Witch]]\n[[Category:Television about magic]]\n[[Category:British television programmes based on children's books]]\n[[Category:2017 German television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2010s German television series]]\n[[Category:Netflix original programming]]\n[[Category:Netflix children's programming]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|the 2017 television series|other series, books and film in The Worst Witch franchise|The Worst Witch (disambiguation)}}\n{{EngvarB|date=November 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = The Worst Witch\n| image                    = Worst Witch Title Card.jpg\n| caption                  = \n| genre                    = [[Fantasy]]\n| creator                  = \n| based_on                 = The original ''[[The Worst Witch]]'' books by [[Jill Murphy]]\n| developer                = \n| writer                   = Emma Reeves\n| director                 = [[Brian Grant (director)|Brian Grant]]\n| creative_director        = \n| starring                 = \n| theme_music_composer     = \n| opentheme                = \n| endtheme                 = \n| composer                 = [[Mark Russell (composer)|Mark Russell]]\n| country                  = United Kingdom<br>Germany\n| language                 = English\n| num_series               = 4\n| num_episodes             = 41\n| executive_producer       = Marcus Wilson<br>Arne Lohmann<br>Nicole Keep<br>Tamara Rothenberg\n| producer                 = Lucy Martin\n| location                 = [[Cheshire]] and [[Germany]]\n| cinematography           = \n| editor                   = David Mercer<br>David Head\n| runtime                  = {{Plainlist|\n* 30 min.\n* 60 min. (episodes 1\u20132)\n}}\n| company                  = [[CBBC|CBBC Productions]]<br />[[ZDF]]\n| distributor              = [[ZDF|ZDF Enterprises]]\n| network                  = [[CBBC]] <small>(UK)</small><br />[[ZDF]] <small>(Germany)</small><br />[[Netflix]] <small>(international)</small>\n| picture_format           = [[High Definition Television|HDTV]] [[1080i]]\n| audio_format             = [[Dolby Digital|Dolby Digital 5.1]]\n| first_aired              = 11 January 2017<ref name=\"TWW-PR\">{{cite press release|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/mediapacks/worstwitch/pupils|title=CBBC brings The Worst Witch to life for a new generation|publisher=BBC Media Centre|date=12 November 2016|accessdate=27 December 2016}}</ref>\n| last_aired               = present\n| preceded_by              = \n| related                  = ''[[The Worst Witch (film)|The Worst Witch]]'' (1986) <br> ''[[The Worst Witch (1998 TV series)|The Worst Witch]]'' (1998\u20132001) <br> ''[[Weirdsister College]]'' (2001) <br> ''[[The New Worst Witch]]'' (2005\u20132007)\n| website                  = https://www.bbc.co.uk/cbbc/shows/the-worst-witch\n}}\n'''''The Worst Witch''''' is a British-German<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2016/dec/18/worst-witch-children-tv-adaptation|title=Harry Potter for girls? I'm not that kind of Worst Witch, says TV's new Mildred Hubble|last=Conlan|first=Tara|date=18 December 2016|website=the Guardian|language=en|access-date=4 February 2018}}</ref> [[fantasy]] children's [[television series]] about a group of young witches at a school for magic. It stars [[Bella Ramsey]] and is based on ''[[The Worst Witch]]'' books by [[Jill Murphy]] (published 1974\u20132018).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/2016/worst-witch-casting|title=BBC \u2013 Cast announced as production begins on CBBC's adaptation of The Worst Witch \u2013 Media Centre|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/news/the-worst-witch-is-getting-a-tv-reboot-a6867706.html|title=The Worst Witch is getting a TV reboot on CBBC|date=11 February 2016|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prolificnorth.co.uk/2016/05/alice-webb-writes-of-her-plans-as-the-new-director-of-bbc-north/|title=\"There's still more to do\" writes Alice Webb the new Director of BBC North|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.radiotimes.com/news/2016-05-16/the-worst-witch-remake-has-cast-its-mildred-hubble|title=The Worst Witch remake has cast its Mildred Hubble|publisher=}}</ref> It is the fifth adaptation of The Worst Witch series after the [[The Worst Witch (film)|1986 television film]], the [[The Worst Witch (1998 TV series)|1998 television series]], the [[Weirdsister College|2001 television spin-off]] and the [[The New Worst Witch|2005 television spin-off]]. \n\nThe series is an [[international co-production]] between [[CBBC]], [[ZDF]] and [[Netflix]]<ref name=\"bbc.co.uk\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/2016/worst-witch-images|title=BBC \u2013 The Worst Witch first look images and sneak peek clip unveiled \u2013 Media Centre|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"variety\"/> The series was made available to stream internationally on Netflix on 22 July 2017. It will be made available to members in the UK, Ireland and Germany after its premiere on CBBC and ZDF.<ref name=\"variety\">{{cite web|title=Netflix Sets Tween Series 'Worst Witch,' 'Horse Mystery Project' For 2017|url=https://variety.com/2016/digital/news/netflix-tween-series-worst-witch-horse-mystery-project-1201849203|website=Variety|accessdate=1 September 2016}}</ref> The series premiered on CBBC on 11 January 2017.<ref name=\"bbc.co.uk\"/> A second series was confirmed in June 2017 and began airing from 8 January 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/2017/childrens-commissions#heading-returning-in-house-drama-cbbc|title=BBC - BBC Children's announce raft of new commissions - Media Centre|website=www.bbc.co.uk}}</ref><ref name=Schedule>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/schedules/p00fzl9r/2018/01/08|title=CBBC Schedule 08/01/18|work=CBBC|date=12 January 2018|accessdate=5 January 2018}}</ref> The second series premiered on [[Netflix]] Australia on 27 July 2018. The third series began airing on 7 January 2019.<ref name=\"bbc_series_3_early_schedule\">{{cite web| url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/genres/childrens/drama/schedules/2019/01/07| title=BBC - Programmes categorised as Children's: Drama, Schedule, Monday 7 January 2019| accessdate=14 March 2019}}</ref> Series 4 began airing on 27 January 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/schedules/p00fzl9r/2020/01/27|title=CBBC - Schedules, Monday 27 January 2020|website=BBC|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-01-23}}</ref>\n\n==Characters==\n<!-- Do NOT add non-main cast to this cast table as per [[WP:TVCAST]] -->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ Cast list of ''The Worst Witch''\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" width=\"14%\" scope=\"col\" | Character\n! rowspan=\"2\" width=\"14%\" scope=\"col\" | Actor\n! rowspan=\"2\" width=\"14%\" scope=\"col\" | Role\n! colspan=\"4\" | Series\n|-\n! width=\"10%\" scope=\"col\"| Series 1\n! width=\"10%\" scope=\"col\"| Series 2\n! width=\"10%\" scope=\u201ccol\"| Series 3\n! width=\"10%\" scope=\"col\"| Series 4\n|-\n| [[The Worst Witch#Miss Cackle|Miss Ada Cackle]]\n| [[Claire Higgins]]\n| Headmistress\n| colspan=4 {{CMain}}\n|-\n| [[The Worst Witch#Miss Hardbroom|Miss Joy Hecate Hardbroom]]\n| [[Raquel Cassidy]]\n| Deputy Headmistress <br> Potions Teacher\n| colspan=4 {{CMain}}\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | [[Mildred Hubble]]\n| [[Bella Ramsey]] (series 1\u20133)\n| rowspan=2 | Student\n| colspan=3 {{CMain}}\n| colspan=1 {{CNone}}\n|-\n| Lydia Page (series 4)\n| colspan=3 {{CNone}}\n| colspan=1 {{CMain}}\n|- \n| Julie Hubble\n